xml:space="preserve" bytes="1033232"> {{Article for deletion/dated|page=List of all National Historic Landmarks|timestamp=20161025174042|year=2016|month=October|day=25|substed=yes}} {{nr|date=October 2016}} {{very long|date=October 2016}} {{underlinked|date=September 2016}} A '''[[National Historic Landmark]]''' ('''NHL''') is a building, [[wiktionary:site|site]], structure, [[National Register of Historic Places property types#Object|object]], or [[National Register of Historic Places property types#Historic districts|district]] that is officially recognized by the [[Federal government of the United States|United States government]] for its outstanding historical significance. Of over 85,000 places listed on the country's [[National Register of Historic Places]], 2500 are recognized as National Historic Landmarks. == Master list == This sortable table allows viewing of all existing and deleted NHLs across all states. == NHL sortable table == {| class="wikitable sortable" |+Sortable table |- !
